    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>IRELAND BANKS IN MERGER TALKS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Brian Lavery</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Lavery, Brian</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ireland's First Active PLC is in talks with Anglo-Irish Bank Corp about possible merger; combination of banks would create Ireland's fourth-largest bank (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A leading mortgage lender in Ireland, First Active P.L.C., is in talks with the Anglo-Irish Bank Corporation about a possible merger. A combination of the banks would create Ireland's fourth-largest banking company with 55 branches in Ireland and Britain. The talks come against a backdrop of intensifying consolidation in Ireland's financial services industry, which faces increased competition from foreign banks.</p>
        <p>Brian Lavery</p>
      </block>
